          "definition": "an unfavorable or disadvantageous position or outcome that one receives in a particular situation",
          "examples": [
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "In this negotiation, it feels like our side is getting the short end of the stick with the unfavorable terms being imposed upon us."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The employees in the company believe they are consistently getting the short end of the stick when it comes to promotions and raises."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Despite their hard work and dedication, marginalized communities often find themselves on the receiving end of the short end of the stick in terms of access to resources and opportunities."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Throughout history, certain groups have received the short end of the stick, facing discrimination and oppression based on their race, gender, or socioeconomic status."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "During the economic recession, many families felt they got the short end of the stick as they struggled to make ends meet while the wealthy seemed unaffected."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "In the previous project, our team got the short end of the stick with the most challenging tasks and tight deadlines."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "If we don't address systemic inequalities, future generations will continue to get the short end of the stick, perpetuating cycles of disadvantage and injustice."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Without proper regulations and oversight, there is a risk that workers will get the short end of the stick in terms of wages and working conditions in the coming years."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The marginalized communities fear they will continue to get the short end of the stick unless proactive measures are taken to address systemic biases and discrimination."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
